SIMPLE: superfetation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superfetation
<hw>Su`per*fe*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>superf⟦eacute⟧tation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The
formation of a fetus at the result of an impregnation occurring after
another impregnation but before the birth of the offspring produced by
it. This is possible only when there is a double uterus, or where
menstruation persists up to the time of the second
impregnation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In then became a <qex>superfetation</qex> upon, and not an
ingredient in, the national character.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superfete</ent>⟦br⟧
